<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11963&amp;p=135971#p135971"><![CDATA[
Yes, the microphone input does work on a Famicom.  However it's not just the microphone by itself that triggers the price haggle -- you have to hold A on controller 2 while saying something into the mic.  I found numerous Japanese websites that say the same thing.<br /><br />In the US/EU release, it was changed to simply look for A+B on controller 2.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Mon Nov 03, 2014 2:49 pm</p><hr />
